<br>
Eh.. I could type a lot more, and I almost started to, but I have other things I would like to do with this day. Thanks for reading. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utriff.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Triff</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.maclem.com/images/triff/triffdot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 573<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/1/02 1:49:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=269.topic&index=303>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Expectations and consequences of God</span><hr size=1> Quick add-on, though—if any of you need an example of the term amoral, think of robots or of natural disasters. You don't think of tornadoes or thunderstorms as evil, because they do not have volition one way or the other. If men have no volition to change whether they are moral or not, then they too are amoral. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulukariatrueheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lukaria Trueheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 123<br> <font color=#E9D756>(3/2/02 12:14:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrfrm18.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=269.topic&index=304>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Expectations and consequences of God</span><hr size=1> Any Christian who claims they personally alone have the cure is fooling you, Lurikeen.  The claims they should make are of the bible and specifically, of Jesus Christ.  Any goodness you see in our lives is a reflection of Christ, and is Him working through us.  Yes I believe that.<br>
